      <h1>
        Less Framework
      </h1>
      <p class='intro'>
        
      </p>
      <p><strong><a href="http://lessframework.com">Less Framework</a> is an adaptive CSS grid system,</strong> and the ancestor of my later grid system: <a href="http://framelessgrid.com">Frameless</a>. It adapts by switching between four static-width layouts, depending on the width of the screen. Each layout shares the same column and gutter widths, making it easy to reuse elements between them.</p>
      
      <p>It was my first attempt to develop an alternative to adaptive fluid-width layouts. A lot of people at the time were also looking for a way out from using fluid layouts, causing Less Framework to become quite popular. I ended up developing four major versions of it.</p>
      
      <p><img src="/images/projects/less-framework.jpg" alt="" /></p>
